{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c4adc9e0-7e6b-4c6d-bff5-37d10a59d5b6","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Action | Events fired |\n|--------|-------------|\n| App launch | Created → Activated |\n| User switches away | Deactivated → Stopped |\n| User returns | Resumed → Activated |\n| App closed | Stopped → Destroying |\n| iOS background snapshot | Backgrounding |\n\n`Backgrounding` is iOS-specific (used for state preservation). All others fire cross-platform. Replace `Debug.WriteLine` with your preferred logger (e.g., `ILogger`, Serilog) for production diagnostics.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a32a992d-c618-43ab-a2c8-94efbddd7767","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about Window lifecycle events in .NET MAUI and how to subscribe to them for debugging/logging purposes. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI that I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":430,"requestId":"E833:12D387:25DACD2:29E56EA:69F93EF8"},"id":"ba51c8d4-e2ba-4961-9ebb-667d671ecac0","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:51:12.903Z","parentId":"05a18c5f-c2b4-4e4a-91a5-f42d9419f602"}
